revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

hpnicfMcsGlobalConfigTable.name: hpnicfMcsGlobalConfigTable
hpnicfMcsGlobalConfigTable.description: Table containing information about the global configuration of IGMP/MLD snooping.

hpnicfMcsGlobalConfigEntry.name: hpnicfMcsGlobalConfigEntry
hpnicfMcsGlobalConfigEntry.description: Entry containing information about the global configuration of IGMP/MLD snooping.

hpnicfMcsGlbSnoopingType.name: hpnicfMcsGlbSnoopingType
hpnicfMcsGlbSnoopingType.description: Type of the global configuration. IPv4 means IGMP snooping configuration, and IPv6 means MLD snooping configuration.

hpnicfMcsGlbRowStatus.name: hpnicfMcsGlbRowStatus
hpnicfMcsGlbRowStatus.description: The activation of a row enables IGMP/MLD snooping globally. The destruction of a row disables IGMP/MLD snooping globally.

hpnicfMcsGlbEntryLimit.name: hpnicfMcsGlbEntryLimit
hpnicfMcsGlbEntryLimit.description: Global maximum number of IGMP/MLD snooping forwarding entries.

hpnicfMcsGlbHostAgingTime.name: hpnicfMcsGlbHostAgingTime
hpnicfMcsGlbHostAgingTime.description: Global aging time of the multicast group on ports.

hpnicfMcsGlbRouterAgingTime.name: hpnicfMcsGlbRouterAgingTime
hpnicfMcsGlbRouterAgingTime.description: Global aging time of router ports.

hpnicfMcsGlbDropUnknownEnabled.name: hpnicfMcsGlbDropUnknownEnabled
hpnicfMcsGlbDropUnknownEnabled.description: Whether the feature of dropping unknown packets is enabled globally.

hpnicfMcsVirtualUnitConfigTable.name: hpnicfMcsVirtualUnitConfigTable
hpnicfMcsVirtualUnitConfigTable.description: Table containing configuration information about the specified VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVirtualUnitConfigEntry.name: hpnicfMcsVirtualUnitConfigEntry
hpnicfMcsVirtualUnitConfigEntry.description: Entry containing information of the specified VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVUID.name: hpnicfMcsVUID
hpnicfMcsVUID.description: VLAN ID or VSI Index. Its value ranges from 1 to 4094 when type is VLAN, and from 0 to 0xFFFFFFFE when type is VSI

hpnicfMcsVUSnoopingType.name: hpnicfMcsVUSnoopingType
hpnicfMcsVUSnoopingType.description: Type of the configuration. IPv4 means IGMP snooping configuration, and IPv6 means MLD snooping configuration.

hpnicfMcsVURowStatus.name: hpnicfMcsVURowStatus
hpnicfMcsVURowStatus.description: The activation of a row enables IGMP/MLD snooping in the VLAN or VSI. The destruction of a row disables IGMP/MLD snooping in the VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVUHostAgingTime.name: hpnicfMcsVUHostAgingTime
hpnicfMcsVUHostAgingTime.description: Aging time of the multicast group on ports in the VLAN or VSI. A value of zero indicates that it is not configured in the VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVUMaxResponseTime.name: hpnicfMcsVUMaxResponseTime
hpnicfMcsVUMaxResponseTime.description: Maximum query response time in the VLAN or VSI. A value of zero indicates that it is not configured in the VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVURouterAgingTime.name: hpnicfMcsVURouterAgingTime
hpnicfMcsVURouterAgingTime.description: Aging time of the router port in the VLAN or VSI. A value of zero indicates that it is not configured in the VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVULastMemQryInterval.name: hpnicfMcsVULastMemQryInterval
hpnicfMcsVULastMemQryInterval.description: Last member query interval in the VLAN or VSI. A value of zero indicates that it is not configured in the VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVUDropUnknownEnabled.name: hpnicfMcsVUDropUnknownEnabled
hpnicfMcsVUDropUnknownEnabled.description: Whether the feature of dropping unknown packets is enabled in the VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVUPimSnoopingEnabled.name: hpnicfMcsVUPimSnoopingEnabled
hpnicfMcsVUPimSnoopingEnabled.description: Whether PIM snooping is enabled in the VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVUVersion.name: hpnicfMcsVUVersion
hpnicfMcsVUVersion.description: Version of IGMP/MLD snooping that is running on the VLAN. Value 2 represents IGMPv2 snooping and MLDv1 snooping, and value 3 represents IGMPv3 snooping and MLDv2 snooping.

hpnicfMcsVUQuerierEnabled.name: hpnicfMcsVUQuerierEnabled
hpnicfMcsVUQuerierEnabled.description: Whether the querier feature is enabled in the VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsVUGeneQuerierSourceAddress.name: hpnicfMcsVUGeneQuerierSourceAddress
hpnicfMcsVUGeneQuerierSourceAddress.description: Source IP address of IGMP or MLD general query packets. Its value is 255.255.255.255 or FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF when not configured.

hpnicfMcsVUSpecQuerierSourceAddress.name: hpnicfMcsVUSpecQuerierSourceAddress
hpnicfMcsVUSpecQuerierSourceAddress.description: Source IP address of IGMP or MLD group-specific query packets. Its value is 255.255.255.255 or FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF when not configured.

hpnicfMcsVULeaveSourceAddress.name: hpnicfMcsVULeaveSourceAddress
hpnicfMcsVULeaveSourceAddress.description: Source IP address of IGMP or MLD leave packets. Its value is 255.255.255.255 or FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF when not configured.

hpnicfMcsVUReportSourceAddress.name: hpnicfMcsVUReportSourceAddress
hpnicfMcsVUReportSourceAddress.description: Source IP address of IGMP or MLD report packets. Its value is 255.255.255.255 or FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF when not configured.

hpnicfMcsL2EntryTable.name: hpnicfMcsL2EntryTable
hpnicfMcsL2EntryTable.description: Table containing a list of Layer 2 multicast group entries.

hpnicfMcsL2EntryEntry.name: hpnicfMcsL2EntryEntry
hpnicfMcsL2EntryEntry.description: Entry of l2-multicast group, which is created for each group learned or configured in the VLAN or VSI.

hpnicfMcsL2EntryVUID.name: hpnicfMcsL2EntryVUID
hpnicfMcsL2EntryVUID.description: VLAN ID or VSI Index. Its value ranges from 1 to 4094 when type is VLAN, and from 0 to 0xFFFFFFFE when type is VSI.

hpnicfMcsL2EntryGroupAddress.name: hpnicfMcsL2EntryGroupAddress
hpnicfMcsL2EntryGroupAddress.description: IP address of the multicast group which the port joined.

hpnicfMcsL2EntrySourceAddress.name: hpnicfMcsL2EntrySourceAddress
hpnicfMcsL2EntrySourceAddress.description: IP address of the unicast source which the port joined.

hpnicfMcsL2EntryIfIndex.name: hpnicfMcsL2EntryIfIndex
hpnicfMcsL2EntryIfIndex.description: IfIndex value of the port that joined the Layer 2 IP multicast group entry.

hpnicfMcsL2EntryPortAttribute.name: hpnicfMcsL2EntryPortAttribute
hpnicfMcsL2EntryPortAttribute.description: Attribute of the port. 'd' means learned from IGMP/MLD packets, 's' means configured statically, 'p' means learned from PIM snooping, 'k' means obtained from the kernel, 'r' means learned from (*, *) entries, 'w' means learned from (*, G) entries.

hpnicfMcsPacketStatisticsTable.name: hpnicfMcsPacketStatisticsTable
hpnicfMcsPacketStatisticsTable.description: Table containing the IGMP/MLD packets statistics.

hpnicfMcsPacketStatisticsEntry.name: hpnicfMcsPacketStatisticsEntry
hpnicfMcsPacketStatisticsEntry.description: Entry containing the statistic information of IGMP/MLD packets that have been transmitted and received in the device.

hpnicfMcsStatisticsSnoopingType.name: hpnicfMcsStatisticsSnoopingType
hpnicfMcsStatisticsSnoopingType.description: Type of the snooping, IPv4 means the statistics for IGMP snooping, and IPv6 means the statistics for MLD snooping.

hpnicfMcsRxGeneryQueryNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxGeneryQueryNum
hpnicfMcsRxGeneryQueryNum.description: Statistics of IGMP or MLD general query packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxV2SpecificQueryNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxV2SpecificQueryNum
hpnicfMcsRxV2SpecificQueryNum.description: Statistics of IGMPv2 or MLDv1 group-specific query packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxV3SpecificQueryNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxV3SpecificQueryNum
hpnicfMcsRxV3SpecificQueryNum.description: The statistics of IGMPv3 or MLDv2 group-specific query packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxV3SpecificSGQueryNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxV3SpecificSGQueryNum
hpnicfMcsRxV3SpecificSGQueryNum.description: Statistics of IGMPv3 or MLDv2 group-and-source-specific query packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxV1ReportNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxV1ReportNum
hpnicfMcsRxV1ReportNum.description: Statistics of IGMPv1 report packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxV2ReportNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxV2ReportNum
hpnicfMcsRxV2ReportNum.description: Statistics of IGMPv2 or MLDv1 report packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxV3ReportNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxV3ReportNum
hpnicfMcsRxV3ReportNum.description: Statistics of IGMPv3 or MLDv2 report packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxV3ErrCorReportNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxV3ErrCorReportNum
hpnicfMcsRxV3ErrCorReportNum.description: Statistics of IGMPv3 or MLDv2 report packets with correct and incorrect records received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxLeaveNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxLeaveNum
hpnicfMcsRxLeaveNum.description: Statistics of leave packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxPimHelloNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxPimHelloNum
hpnicfMcsRxPimHelloNum.description: Statistics of PIM hello packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsRxErrorPacketNum.name: hpnicfMcsRxErrorPacketNum
hpnicfMcsRxErrorPacketNum.description: Statistics of error IGMP/MLD packets received on the device.

hpnicfMcsTxV2SpecificQueryNum.name: hpnicfMcsTxV2SpecificQueryNum
hpnicfMcsTxV2SpecificQueryNum.description: Statistics of IGMPv2 or MLDv1 group-specific query packets sent from the device.

hpnicfMcsTxV3SpecificQueryNum.name: hpnicfMcsTxV3SpecificQueryNum
hpnicfMcsTxV3SpecificQueryNum.description: Statistics of IGMPv3 or MLDv2 group-specific query packets sent from the device.

hpnicfMcsTxV3SpecificSGQueryNum.name: hpnicfMcsTxV3SpecificSGQueryNum
hpnicfMcsTxV3SpecificSGQueryNum.description: Statistics of IGMPv3 or MLDv2 group-and-source-specific query packets sent from the device.

hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupConfigTable.name: hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupConfigTable
hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupConfigTable.description: Table for configuring a port as a simulated member host for a multicast group.

hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupConfigEntry.name: hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupConfigEntry
hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupConfigEntry.description: Entry for configuring a port as a simulated member host for a multicast group.

hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupIfIndex.name: hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupIfIndex
hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupIfIndex.description: Port for which this entry contains information.

hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupSnoopingType.name: hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupSnoopingType
hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupSnoopingType.description: Type of the configuration. IPv4 means IGMP snooping configuration, and IPv6 means MLD snooping configuration.

hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupVlanID.name: hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupVlanID
hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupVlanID.description: Index uniquely identifying the specified VLAN in which a host on a port joined the multicast group.

hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupGroupAddress.name: hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupGroupAddress
hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupGroupAddress.description: IP address of the group to which the host belongs.

hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupSourceAddress.name: hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupSourceAddress
hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupSourceAddress.description: IP address of the source. A value of zero indicates that the multicast packets of this group can come from any sources.

hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupStatus.name: hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupStatus
hpnicfMcsPortJoinGroupStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing rows, which supports 'active', 'createAndGo' and 'destroy'.

hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupConfigTable.name: hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupConfigTable
hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupConfigTable.description: Table for configuring static group membership entries on a port.

hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupConfigEntry.name: hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupConfigEntry
hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupConfigEntry.description: Entry for configuring static group membership entries on a port.

hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupIfIndex.name: hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupIfIndex
hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupIfIndex.description: Port for which this entry contains information.

hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupSnoopingType.name: hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupSnoopingType
hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupSnoopingType.description: Type of the configuration. IPv4 means IGMP snooping configuration, and IPv6 means MLD snooping configuration.

hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupVlanID.name: hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupVlanID
hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupVlanID.description: Index uniquely identifying the specified VLAN in which a port statically joined the multicast group.

hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupGroupAddress.name: hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupGroupAddress
hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupGroupAddress.description: IP address of the multicast group.

hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupSourceAddress.name: hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupSourceAddress
hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupSourceAddress.description: IP address of the source. A value of zero indicates that the multicast packets of this group can come from any sources.

hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupStatus.name: hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupStatus
hpnicfMcsPortStaticGroupStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation and deletion of rows, which supports 'active', 'createAndGo' and 'destroy'.

hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigTable.name: hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigTable
hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigTable.description: Table for configuring a port as a static router port.

hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigEntry.name: hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigEntry
hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigEntry.description: Entry for configuring a port as a static router port.

hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigIfIndex.name: hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigIfIndex
hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigIfIndex.description: Port for which this entry contains information.

hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigSnoopingType.name: hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigSnoopingType
hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigSnoopingType.description: Type of the configuration. IPv4 means IGMP snooping configuration, and IPv6 means MLD snooping configuration.

hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigVlanID.name: hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigVlanID
hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigVlanID.description: Index uniquely identifying the specified VLAN in which a port act as a static router port.

hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigRowStatus.name: hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigRowStatus
hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigRowStatus.description: This object is a conceptual row entry that allows to add or delete entries to or from the hpnicfMcsRouterPortConfigTable. When an entry is created in this table 'createAndGo' method is used and the value of this object is set to 'active'. Deactivation of an 'active' entry is not allowed. When an entry is deleted in this table 'destroy' method is used.

hpnicfMcsPortConfigTable.name: hpnicfMcsPortConfigTable
hpnicfMcsPortConfigTable.description: Table for configuring the fast leave status, group limit number, group policy parameter and overflow replace status on a port in the specified VLAN.

hpnicfMcsPortConfigEntry.name: hpnicfMcsPortConfigEntry
hpnicfMcsPortConfigEntry.description: Entry containing information about the fast leave status, group limit number, group policy parameter and overflow replace status of a port in the specified VLAN.

hpnicfMcsPortConfigIfIndex.name: hpnicfMcsPortConfigIfIndex
hpnicfMcsPortConfigIfIndex.description: Port for which this entry contains information.

hpnicfMcsPortConfigSnoopingType.name: hpnicfMcsPortConfigSnoopingType
hpnicfMcsPortConfigSnoopingType.description: Type of the configuration. IPv4 means IGMP snooping configuration, and IPv6 means MLD snooping configuration.

hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupLimitNumber.name: hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupLimitNumber
hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupLimitNumber.description: Group limit number of the port.

hpnicfMcsPortConfigFastLeaveStatus.name: hpnicfMcsPortConfigFastLeaveStatus
hpnicfMcsPortConfigFastLeaveStatus.description: Fast leave status of the port.

hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupPolicyParameter.name: hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupPolicyParameter
hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupPolicyParameter.description: ACL number which is used as the group policy parameter of the port.

hpnicfMcsPortConfigOverflowReplace.name: hpnicfMcsPortConfigOverflowReplace
hpnicfMcsPortConfigOverflowReplace.description: This object is related to the object hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupLimitNumber. If the current group number is less than the value of hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupLimitNumber, any new group is permitted. If the current group number equals to the value of hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupLimitNumber and the value of this object is enabled, the group with the minimum multicast address will be replaced by the new group. If the current group number equals to the value of hpnicfMcsPortConfigGroupLimitNumber and the value of this object is disabled, none of new group will be permitted.

hpnicfMcsPortConfigRowStatus.name: hpnicfMcsPortConfigRowStatus
hpnicfMcsPortConfigRowStatus.description: The object is responsible for managing the creation and deletion of rows, which supports 'active', 'createAndGo' and 'destroy'.
